# .forceignore — tells the Salesforce CLI what NOT to deploy
#
# Similar to .gitignore but for Salesforce metadata deployments.
# Any file or pattern listed here is skipped when you run:
#   sf project deploy start --target-org <alias>
#
# Without this file, the CLI would try to deploy non-metadata files
# (like README_SETUP.md) and fail with an error.

# ── Documentation files inside the salesforce/ directory ─────────────────────
salesforce/README_SETUP.md

# ── OS and editor noise ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
**/.DS_Store
**/.idea
**/.vscode
**/node_modules

# ── SFDX internal files (auto-generated, not deployable metadata) ─────────────
.sfdx/
.sf/
